he Module System helps split a large application into independent modules with clear dependencies.

Without Modules
...........................
In a banking application:

Banking Application
|
|-- Account Service
|-- Customer Service
|-- Loan Service
|-- Payment Service

All classes are accessible everywhere.

Problems:
..............................
 Tight coupling
 Difficult maintenance
 No strong encapsulation

With Modules
bank-account
bank-customer
bank-loan
bank-payment

Each module exposes only required packages.
........................................
Module: bank-account
...........................
..........................
module-info.java
module bank.account {
    exports com.bank.account.service;
}

Service Class

package com.bank.account.service;

public class AccountService {

    public void createAccount() {
        System.out.println("Account Created");
    }
}

Module: bank-loan
...........................
module-info.java
module bank.loan {

    requires bank.account;
}

Loan Service
;...................
package com.bank.loan.service;

import com.bank.account.service.AccountService;

public class LoanService {

    public static void main(String[] args) {

        AccountService service =
                new AccountService();

        service.createAccount();
    }
}
